23/05/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- More than 300 people took part in a gay parade in Bucharest on Saturday (May 22nd). 
The participants marched in the capital's centre amid heavy police presence. 
The Gay Fest parade has received strong support from 11 embassies in the country. 
UK ambassador Robin Barnett was one of the participants. 
Hours before the event, 150 representatives of far-right organisations held a protest against homosexuality. 
(Mediafax, AFP, AP, Reuters - 22/05/10)
